snippet.textDisplay: So, here's a trick that I learned on accident for dealing with the "you can only poop during this window of time". The solution is, Stop drinking anything with caffeine , cold-turkey, except for about 5 minutes before the start of that window of time.  Caffeine Withdrawal makes you constipated, but then relieving that withdrawal, overstimulates the bowels. Caffeine withdrawal takes about 5-6 days to end before you're back to normal. Doesn't matter if it's coke, coffee, tea, or monster. If you exclusively drink it during a specific window of time in the day, of like, 1 hour, and then cold turkey for the rest of the time, you'll end up only pooping when you have caffeine, or more accurately, Always poop when you have caffeine. but you have to follow that type of schedule, and just deal with the other caffeine withdrawal stuff, the cravings, maybe headaches, general irritability. your body hates it, but probably not as much as mixing laxatives with whatever the opposite of a laxative is.
